    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your slow cooker and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Turn on your<strong> slow cooker </strong>to high</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-diced-pork-stout-and-mushroom-stew/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferable non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced pork shoulder </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until the pork is lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-diced-pork-stout-and-mushroom-stew/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>into discs on the diagonal</p><p>Chop your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-diced-pork-stout-and-mushroom-stew/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the <strong>onion wedges</strong>, <strong>sliced carrot </strong>and <strong>chopped mushrooms </strong>and cook for 2 min or until starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-diced-pork-stout-and-mushroom-stew/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> into quarters</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-diced-pork-stout-and-mushroom-stew/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add your <strong>tomato paste </strong>and the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and<strong> </strong>give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add your <strong>stout paste </strong>and <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>with 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and bring to the boil over a high heat and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-diced-pork-stout-and-mushroom-stew/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, transfer everything from the pan to the <strong>slow cooker</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potato</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up, then cover and cook on high for 4 hours \u2013 this is your <strong>slow cooker pork, stout & mushroom stew</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if the stew is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-diced-pork-stout-and-mushroom-stew/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>slow cooker pork, stout & mushroom stew </strong>in a bowl</p><p>Season with a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
